usband%2C%20whose%20extended%20family%20throws%20reunions%20that%20are%20essentially%20small%20festivals%2C%20didn't%20find%20it%20funny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205605b40-67dc-4bc1-91c3-dea1a09c6436%5C%22%3EMy%20husband%20wanted%20me%20to%20take%20his%20last%20name%2C%20while%20I%20was%20ambivalent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20that%20I%20was%20emotionally%20tied%20to%20my%20previous%20last%20name.%20Saying%20and%20spelling%20%26quot%3BChilds%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life%20was%20just%20easier%20than%20%26quot%3BNieslanik%26quot%3B.%20Not%20to%20mention%2C%20it%20feels%20weird%20to%20think%20of%20yourself%20as%20one%20person%20with%20one%20name%20for%20so%20many%20years%2C%20only%20to%20change%20that.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-didnt-change-my-last-name-after-marriage-how-its-going%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMy%20name%20was%20a%20fundamental%20part%20of%20who%20I%20was%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20change%20it%20in%20my%20mid-thirties%20felt%20strange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20at%20wedding%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6830aa30c6ad288d1481cb19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22685%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20changed%20her%20last%20name%20to%20her%20husband's%20after%20getting%20married.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20there%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fhow-to-report-name-change-to-credit-bureau%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebureaucratic%20red%20tape%20that%20comes%20with%20changing%20your%20name%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Birth%20certificate%2C%20driver's%20license%2C%20passport%2C%20and%20bills.%20Changing%20your%20name%20is%20like%20updating%20your%20entire%20identity%20one%20tedious%20form%20at%20a%20time.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20though%2C%20I%20knew%20how%20much%20it%20would%20mean%20to%20my%20husband%20if%20I%20took%20his%20last%20name.%20And%20part%20of%20that%20was%20because%20I%20had%20already%20changed%20my%20name%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b9ce61c-55f0-4ebb-9266-9daf9ae42d3e%5C%22%3EIt%20wasn't%20my%20first%20last%20name%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20last%20name%20when%20I%20met%20my%20husband%20wasn't%20the%20one%20I%20was%20born%20with.%20Ironically%2C%20in%20my%20late%20teens%2C%20I'd%20already%20gone%20through%20a%20name%20change%20after%20a%20short-lived%20first%20marriage.%20My%20maiden%20name%20had%20been%20a%20mouthful%20that%20people%20always%20messed%20up%2C%20so%20adopting%20a%20simpler%20one%20was%20a%20relief.%20Plus%2C%20no%20one%20in%20my%20immediate%20family%20shared%20my%20last%20name.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-maiden-name-middle-names-family-legacy-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emom%20had%20given%20me%20her%20maiden%20name%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20she%20remarried%20and%20took%20my%20stepfather's%20last%20name%2C%20as%20did%20my%20half-brother%2C%20whom%20they%20had%20together.%20I%20was%20the%20only%20one%20left%20with%20a%20hard%20name%20no%20one%20else%20seemed%20to%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20I%20had%20changed%20my%20name%20before%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20reason%2C%20didn't%20sit%20well%20with%20my%20soon-to-be%20husband.%20If%20I%20had%20changed%20it%20before%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20why%20wouldn't%20I%20be%20willing%20to%20change%20it%20again%3F%20This%20time%2C%20for%20him.%20It%20felt%20like%20a%20personal%20slight%2C%20which%20I%20understood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20that%2C%20my%20husband%20comes%20from%20a%20large%2C%20close-knit%20family%20who%20do%20all%20share%20the%20same%20last%20name.%20Every%20summer%2C%20they%20gather%20in%20the%20hundreds%20for%20a%20family%20reunion%20and%20have%20streets%20named%20after%20them%20in%20towns%20sprinkled%20across%20the%20Western%20Slope%20of%20Colorado.%20As%20an%20only%20child%2C%20he%20felt%20we%20needed%20to%20carry%20on%20the%20name%20for%20his%20family%20branch%20by%20having%20me%20take%20his%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20a%20strong%20internal%20belief%20that%20members%20of%20the%20same%20family%20should%20have%20the%20same%20name.%20Although%20his%20family%20is%20relatively%20liberal%2C%20they%20shared%20the%20cultural%20expectation%20that%20a%20woman%20takes%20her%20husband's%20name%20when%20they%20marry.%20And%20he%20had%20some%20pride%20wrapped%20up%20in%20the%20idea%20that%20I%20would%20carry%20his%20name%E2%80%94that%20when%20people%20met%20us%2C%20they%20would%20know%20that%20we%20belonged%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224608d67a-70a1-490d-820e-924dea79b3c9%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20mind%20that%20I%20changed%20my%20name%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20I%20had%20no%20strong%20objections%2C%20I%20did%20end%20up%20changing%20my%20name%2C%20and%20I%20never%20really%20looked%20back.%20I%20used%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.missnowmrs.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eservice%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20helped%20me%20change%20all%20my%20accounts%2C%20IDs%2C%20and%20paperwork%20in%20one%20(mostly)%20easy%20go%2C%20so%20the%20hassle%20was%20more%20minimal%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20posing%20for%20a%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6830aac3c6ad288d1481cb30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20couple's%20last%20name%20is%20so%20uncommon%20that%20they%20are%20easy%20to%20recognize.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20I%20see%20several%20upsides%20to%20having%20changed%20my%20last%20name.%20For%20example%2C%20it's%20uncommon%2C%20so%20I%20rarely%20get%20confused%20with%20anyone%20else.%20As%20a%20writer%2C%20I%20find%20that%20beneficial.%20I%20like%20having%20the%20same%20last%20name%20as%20our%20children%2C%20and%20I'm%20glad%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20think%20about%20whose%20name%20we%20should%20give%20them%20or%20if%20we%20should%20hyphenate.%20And%20I've%20realized%20that%20my%20last%20name%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20personality.%20If%20that%20means%20I%20have%20to%20spell%20it%20an%20extra%20time%20or%20two%2C%20the%20trade-off%20is%20now%20worth%20it%20in%20my%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223054d99a-ed1d-4de3-8a2a-847ca8535a1a%5C%22%3EThese%20days%2C%20however%2C%20my%20husband%20has%20had%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20about%20the%20situation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20my%20husband%20apologized%20to%20me%20for%20%26quot%3Bmaking%26quot%3B%20me%20change%20my%20name.%20He%20mentioned%20how%20silly%20he%20thought%20his%20reasonings%20were%20now%2C%20that%20he%20understood%20having%20the%20same%20last%20name%20is%20kind%20of%20arbitrary.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20affects%20literally%20no%20part%20of%20our%20lives%20together%20in%20a%20substantial%20way.%20My%20favorite%20realization%20that%20he%20mentioned%20was%20how%20our%20love%20is%20so%20much%20greater%20than%20a%20shared%20last%20name.%20Then%2C%20he%20asked%20if%20I'd%20like%20to%20change%20my%20name%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thought%20of%20returning%20to%20the%20ease%20of%20%26quot%3BChilds%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20last%20name%20has%20its%20appeal%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20help%20but%20laugh.%20I%20have%20zero%20desire%20to%20go%20through%20that%20paperwork%20again.%20Not%20unless%20he%20wants%20to%20revisit%20that%20original%20idea%20of%20picking%20a%20brand-new%20name%20together.%20And%20he's%20willing%20to%20file%20the%20forms%20himself%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-last-name-because-husband-asked-me-to-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A175182108200